body.p:
2. The want of burial is considered as a terrible
calamity. (Isaiah XIV 19.20; Psalms LXXIX 3;
Ecclesiastes VI 3.)

1st The appropriation of any portion of the corpse for

                purposes of gain, or private use of any kind. This is
 prohibited, Yaddim IV. 6;
                Sanhedr. fol. 47, 48,
 Chulin, fol. 122; Niddah 55a;
                Yorah Deah, Chap. 349.

2nd Disinterment likewise prohibited. Baba Bathrah,
fol. 154; Abel Rabbathi, IV. 12; Joreh-Deah cap. 363;
Chosen-Mishpat, cap. 235, §13.

which disinterment is the reverse of desecration;
but as this is irrelevant at present to the point
at issue, I will not farther pursue it.
